main event: Several unidentified objects were observed in the Hawaiian Islands on June 18, 1966.
interesting points: Objects appeared to originate from a bright flash and left a short vapor trail,Observations varied in description and duration,Reports indicated the objects as red streaks trailing fire,Witnesses considered highly reliable reported the objects travelled too fast for conventional aircraft and too slow for meteors,At least one object exploded with a bright flash during the observation.
witness description: personnel on ship and in the air, including a bow watch on USNS Longview
